		"ItemTooltips"
		{
			"item_boots"		"The first thing you want to do on your lane is to zone opponent away with Arctic Burn, get as much lasthits as possible and get early Boots for yourself. Wyvern is pretty slow hero, so this additional mobility early on is crusual for both your attack and defence."
			"item_force_staff"		"Additional mobility/save with a higher potential than Lance early on"
			"item_hurricane_pike"		"Natural upgrade to Force Staff. Allowes us to get better position and zone opponents from miles away"
			"item_maelstrom"		"Additional increase in our farming capabilities, as well as boosting our teamfight damage. You  can get it before pike if you're sure you won't need stats and positioning"
			"item_mjollnir"		"Relatively cheap upgrade with huge damage boost (from attack speed and active ability)"
			"item_soul_ring"		"You can get it instead of one of null talismans as your mana sustain, but considering Offlane Wyvern being all about winning the lane and getting all-in on damage output, you will sell it pretty soon"
			"item_hand_of_midas"		"If you're still successfully winning your lane, but not sure about being able to finish in first 5-10 minutes, you can get Midas after Force Staff, so you'll be able to keep up later on. Altho, you already farm pretty quickly with Mjolnir and you don't want to spend 2k gold on an item that doesn't help you in fights."
			"item_blink"		"Agressive positioning solution, helps with better positioning for your ults (and future Hex)"
			"item_cyclone"		"Cheap mobility and mana regen. Can be good in case if you're playing against Kunkka or some sort of silences"
			"item_bloodthorn"		"Huge mana regen and damage boost. Active ability has pretty good synergy with Winter's Curse (you just need to use it on the ult's target at a proper time to maximize damage output), but the main reason to pick it up is great passive stats that give us everything our hero needs"
			"item_ultimate_scepter"		"Increasing our attack range drastically, as well as making our attack animation faster and removing arctiv burn stack limit is that strong so the whole idea of core Winter Wyvern was born out of it. Altho, you can't get it straight away since you need some kind of mobility item, mana regen item, attack speed item and all this while establishing dominance on the map."
			"item_sheepstick"		"Continuing the theme of mana regen and int items, Scythe is the great addition, that also gives a good utility as well with its active."
			"item_greater_crit"		"Cheap offensive option if you want to get more damage, but don't really want to delay the game too much and won't be able to get top-tier alternatives"
			"item_nullifier"		"Rarely needed since you should have enough lockdown and damage and you Scythe is better in most cases, while Nullifier projectile is pretty slow and you're going to stay away in fights. Altho, it can work in combination with blink or Winter's Curse (use it right at the end of your ultimate, so enemy won't be able to dodge it)"
			"item_bloodstone"		"One of the most popular solutions for enabling Aghs build early on in terms of mana regen. Altho, it gives only mana regen/mana pool and HP boost."
			"item_sphere"		"OK-ish item to get if you're being locked down a bit too much or playing againstDoom"
			"item_black_king_bar"		"...but BKB is usually better choice against lockdown than Linkens"
			"item_shivas_guard"		"OK-ish choice if you need armor. It's not really good item for core Wyvern since you need to get other stuff first, and when it comes to Shivas, you will usually be attacking from too far away for it to get benefit from it (as well as AC)"
			"item_mask_of_madness"		"Good item to increase attack speed drastically for a short period when you really need it. Works well when you have a mana item, Mjolnir and Aghs"
			"item_monkey_king_bar"		"vs Miss chance"
			"item_solar_crest"		"Cheap replacement for Orchid/Bloodthorn"
			"item_yasha_and_kaya"		"Offensive replacement for Euls. Manacost reduction and attack speed are very valuable for Wyvern and she doesn't need to go for Sange and Kaya since she's naturally pretty tanky."
		}
